  "instructions": [
    "In a large mixing bowl, combine rye flour, warm water, and salt. Mix until a shaggy dough forms.",
    "Knead the dough for 5 minutes until smooth and elastic.",
    "Cover the dough with plastic wrap and let rest for 30 minutes.",
    "Divide the dough into 8 equal pieces.",
    "Roll each piece into a thin circle, about 1/8 inch thick.",
    "Heat a large non-stick skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil and swirl to coat.",
    "Cook the blintzes for 2 minutes on each side, until golden brown.",
    "Repeat with the remaining dough pieces.",
    "In a small bowl, mix together powdered sugar and chopped fresh dill.",
    "Serve the blintzes warm with a dollop of sugar-dill mixture and a side of filling (see below)."
  ],
